investigation.title: Rodent Research-1 (RR1) National Lab Validation Flight: Mouse liver transcriptomic, proteomic, epigenomic and histology data
investigation.description: The Rodent Reasearch-1 National Lab (RR-1 CASIS) experiment was performed to study the effect of microgravity on muscle wasting. RNA, DNA, and protein were purified from RR-1 CASIS (the Center for the Advancement of Science in Space) liver samples.

project.title: Rodent Research-1(RR-1), Muscle Atrophy of Muscle Sparing in Transgenic Mice (CASIS RR1)
project.funding: This investigation was funded by the ISS National Lab, the NASA Space Biology Program Office, Space Life and Physical Sciences Research and Applications Division and additional funding from the International Space Station Research Integration Office to the Space Biology GeneLab Project
